This is a known breaking change. Android 15 (API 35) enforces **edge-to-edge** display, so `SOFT_INPUT_ADJUST_RESIZE` is ignored. The fix is to react to **IME window insets** instead.

### Solution

**1. In `Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs`**, attach an insets listener:

```csharp
using Android.OS;
using Android.Views;
using AndroidX.Core.View;
using Microsoft.Maui.Platform;

public class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity
{
    protected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)
    {
        base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);

        var rootView = Window!.DecorView.FindViewById(Android.Resource.Id.Content)!;

        ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(rootView, new ImeInsetsListener());
    }

    private class ImeInsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener
    {
        public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(View view, WindowInsetsCompat insets)
        {
            var imeInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());
            var navInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.NavigationBars());

            // Use the larger of IME or nav-bar bottom inset
            int bottom = Math.Max(imeInsets.Bottom, navInsets.Bottom);

            view.SetPadding(0, 0, 0, bottom);

            return insets;
        }
    }
}
```

**2. Keep `adjustResize`** in `AndroidManifest.xml` (it still signals intent to the insets system):

```xml
<activity android:windowSoftInputMode="adjustResize" ... />
```

**3. Remove the old API call** — delete any `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` usage from your XAML or code-behind.

### Why this works

| .NET 9 / API < 35 | .NET 10 / API 35+ |
|-|-|
| OS auto-resized the window | App draws edge-to-edge; OS sends **insets** |
| `AdjustResize` shrunk the layout | You read `Ime()` insets and apply padding yourself |

The `ImeInsetsListener` detects the keyboard height and pushes your content up by exactly that amount, so your input bar stays visible above the keyboard. No iOS changes are needed — iOS `KeyboardAutoManagerScroll` still handles this automatically.
